The paper discusses a new approach for evolutionary computation using haploid-diploid representations, which is relevant to the field of neural networks and genetic algorithms (cs.NE). It also touches upon fitness landscape ruggedness, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper proposes a new method for recombination, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY).
